        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 5:51PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 551 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Bullard, or 7 miles
west of Jeffersonville, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Jeffersonville, Robins AFB, Marion, Tarversville, District Path,
Myricks Mill, Bullard, Fitzpatrick, Ripley, and Huber.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
